message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper discusses the recent advances in machine learning, specifically deep learning, applied to medical image processing and analysis, with a focus on MRI. This makes it highly likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of deep learning in medical diagnostics and healthcare, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which could also make it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
